ter what is wrong with her or how complicated it makes that process, college guys would still want to sleep with her.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternateUniverse" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AlternateUniverse">Alternate Universe</a>: The heroes, including Gorgon, Banzai, and others, are in a world where there never was a zombie apocalypse. However, clues start popping up to suggest that this world is more than it seems.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnArmAndALeg" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AnArmAndALeg">An Arm and a Leg</a>: This was how they defeated Gibbs; he saw it as penance for falling under Smith's control</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndIMustScream">And I Must Scream</a>: This seems to be what happened to Christian Nguyen.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ArsonMurderAndJaywalking">Arson, Murder, and Jaywalking</a>: After Stealth calls him and asks if he could meet them in Los Angeles, Barry thinks about all of the things he has to do. The casual meeting he was supposed to have with Mike from maintenance about the smell. Jerry and Vanessa talking about component testing schedules. Keith asking for reports. His weekly Warhammer game with the guys down at the store.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BackFromTheDead" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BackFromTheDead">Back from the Dead</a>: Played with. A few previously dead characters, including Gorgon, Banzai, Dr. Sorenson and Jarvis, show up in the alternate reality, but as the entire thing is in the heroes' minds, it's technically only their mental projections of those characters.</li><li> <a class="twikilink" href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton" title="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BerserkButton">Berserk Button</a>: After a minor <a class="twikilink" href